Video Demonstration of Functionality: https://youtu.be/3JhWxVCB0g0

How to execute program:

  Database Setup (pgAdmin4/PostgreSQL):
    1. Ensure that pgAdmin4 and PostgreSQL is installed.
    2. Create a new database named Assignment3.
    3. Open the query tool in the new database.
    4. Click the open file icon, and select the included DDL.sql file.
    5. Run the script with the play button. 
    6. Click the open file icon again, this time selecting the included DML.sql file.
    7. Run the script with the play button. The database is now setup.

  Running the program with IntelliJ IDEA:
    1. Ensure IntelliJ IDEA CE is installed.
    2. Open IntelliJ, then click file and then open.
    3. Select the Submission folder to open.
    4. When asked "open as project?" choose yes.
    5. In the Main.java file, ensure that the String user and String password variables match your username and password of your PostgreSQL server respectively.
    6. Run the program with coverage by clicking the 3 dots at the top right and selecting "Run 'Main' with Coverage"
    7. The provided tests will run. PLEASE NOTE: If you wish to correctly rerun the tests again, you must input the following command into the query tool on pgAdmin4 in the Assignment 3 database in order to reset the sequence counter: ALTER SEQUENCE students_student_id_seq RESTART WITH 4;